    }
}
```

---

### üìå Why Use Encapsulation?

| Benefit             | Explanation |
|---------------------|-------------|
| ‚úÖ Data Hiding       | Prevent direct access to internal data |
| ‚úÖ Controlled Access | Only safe operations are allowed via getters/setters |
| ‚úÖ Code Maintainability | Changes to internal code don‚Äôt affect external usage |
| ‚úÖ Increased Security | Validations can be applied in setter methods |

---

### üß† Summary:

| Feature          | Encapsulation Example       |
|------------------|-----------------------------|
| Private Data     | `private int age;`          |
| Access Control   | `public void setAge(int a)` |
| Data Hiding      | Yes                         |
| Implementation   | Achieved via **classes**, **getters/setters** |

