In **Java**, a class can **inherit from another class** (using `extends`) and **implement one or more interfaces** (using `implements`) **at the same time**.

This is how Java allows a form of **multiple inheritance** ‚Äî a class can **inherit from one superclass** and **many interfaces**.

---

### ‚úÖ Syntax Example: Class + Interface Inheritance

```java
// Interface 1
interface Flyable {
    void fly();
}

// Interface 2
interface Swimmable {
    void swim();
}

// Parent class
class Animal {
    void eat() {
        System.out.println("This animal eats food.");
    }
}

// Child class inherits Animal and implements both interfaces
class Bird extends Animal implements Flyable, Swimmable {
    public void fly() {
        System.out.println("Bird is flying.");
    }

    public void swim() {
        System.out.println("Bird is swimming.");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Bird b = new Bird();
        b.eat();    // inherited from Animal class
        b.fly();    // from Flyable interface
        b.swim();   // from Swimmable interface
    }
}
```

---

### üí° Key Rules:

| Feature | `extends` | `implements` |
|--------|-----------|--------------|
| Used for | Inheriting from a class | Implementing interface(s) |
| Supports multiple? | ‚ùå No (only one class) | ‚úÖ Yes (multiple interfaces) |
| Access modifiers | Can have `public`, `protected`, etc. | All methods are `public abstract` by default |
| Constructors | Inherited from class only | Not allowed in interface |

---

### ‚úÖ Example Summary:
```java
class ChildClass extends SuperClass implements Interface1, Interface2 {
    // class body
}
```

- `extends` ‚Üí used for class-to-class inheritance
- `implements` ‚Üí used for interface-to-class implementation

---

### üîÑ Combining Interface and Class:
You **can‚Äôt** extend more than one class:
```java
class A {}
class B {}
class C extends A, B {} // ‚ùå Not allowed
```

But you **can** do:
```java
class C extends A implements I1, I2 {} // ‚úÖ Allowed
```

