  - \(n\) = number of strings
  - \(L\) = length of the first string (or shortest string in the worst case)  
  This is because in the worst case, we may compare each character in the first string with all other strings.

- **Space complexity:**  
  $$O(1)$$  
  No additional data structures are used (ignoring the output string).  
  If counting the output string of length \(k\), then space complexity is $$O(k)$$.

