## üî∑ Marker Interface

A **marker interface** is an interface that has **no methods or fields**. It is used to provide **metadata** to classes.

Example: `Serializable`, `Cloneable`, `Remote`.

```java
interface Marker {}

class MyClass implements Marker {
    // Used to mark this class for a specific purpose (e.g., serialization)
}
```

