Nice! Integrating a **UPI payment gateway** into your web app adds a real-world feature ‚Äî but here‚Äôs the deal: for **actual payments**, you'll need a backend (Node, Django, etc.) and a gateway provider like Razorpay, PhonePe, or Paytm.

Since you're doing this **without Django for now**, I‚Äôll show you how to **integrate Razorpay UPI** in **frontend-only** (test mode):

---

### ‚úÖ Step-by-step Razorpay UPI Integration (Frontend Only)

#### 1. **Add Razorpay Script to HTML**

In your `<head>` section:

```html
<script src="https://checkout.razorpay.com/v1/checkout.js"></script>
```

#### 2. **Add a "Pay Now" Button in Cart Section**

Under the "Clear Cart" button, add this:

```html
<button class="clear-cart" style="background: #2d8dd6;" onclick="payNow()">Pay Now</button>
```

#### 3. **Add Razorpay Config to Your `<script>`**

Put this function in your script, after `renderCart()`:

```js
function payNow() {
  const totalAmount = Object.values(cart).reduce((acc, item) => acc + item.price * item.quantity, 0);
  if (totalAmount <= 0) {
    alert("Your cart is empty!");
    return;
  }

  const options = {
    key: "rzp_test_YourTestKeyHere", // üîë Replace with your Razorpay Test Key
    amount: totalAmount * 100, // in paise
    currency: "INR",
    name: "Canteen",
    description: "Canteen Order Payment",
    image: "https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/512/3075/3075977.png",
    handler: function (response) {
      alert("Payment successful! ID: " + response.razorpay_payment_id);
      clearCart();
    },
    prefill: {
      name: "Student",
      email: "student@example.com",
      contact: "9999999999"
    },
    theme: {
      color: "#28a745"
    },
    method: {
      upi: true,
      card: false,
      netbanking: false,
      wallet: false
    }
  };

  const rzp = new Razorpay(options);
  rzp.open();
}
```

